      {
        "id": 3311564,
        "name": "Laurent Gibet",
        "username": "Laurent_Gibet",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/2bfe46/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2022-01-07T09:05:44.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong>Chypre Etko (Jorge Ordonez) Commandaria St-Nicholas 2017 : 17/20 \u2013 6/1/2022</strong><br>\nGreen reflections, like for a Mad\u00e8re. Superb rancio (fig, dried date, baklava). Yummy balance, good acidity, average alcohol (15\u00b0).<br>\nMavro (red) et xynisteri (whites grapes), with dessication (then a light fortification). The impression to taste a VDN Roussillon, something like a mix of tuil\u00e9 (red) and ambr\u00e9 (white).</p>\n<p>I also formerly liked the cuv\u00e9e Centurion.</p>",
